---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Denmark immigration fiscal impact: official Ministry of Finance data | Immigration Factbook"
  lang="en"
  altHref="/faq/denmark-fiscal-impact/"
  description="Denmark's Finance Ministry (2023) puts the net fiscal cost of immigrants and descendants at −DKK 16bn/year. Non-Western: −27bn; Western: +11bn. Official primary data only."
>

<!-- ── Hero ── -->
<div class="faq-hero">
  <div class="faq-hero__badge">Official primary source · Finansministeriet 2023</div>
  <h1>Denmark: net fiscal cost of immigration<br><em>−DKK 16 billion per year</em></h1>
  <p class="faq-hero__sub">Denmark's Finance Ministry (Finansministeriet) publishes the most comprehensive official accounting of immigration's net fiscal effect in Europe — broken down by origin, residence duration, and generation.</p>
  <div class="faq-hero__meta">
    <a href="/faq/denmark-fiscal-impact/" class="lang-pill">🌐 日本語版</a>
    <span class="meta-sep">·</span>
    <span class="meta-source">Source: Finansministeriet 2023 (2019 data, revised Sept. 2023)</span>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ── Key figures ── -->
<div class="faq-body">
  <div class="key-stats-row">
    <div class="kstat kstat--cost">
      <div class="kstat__value">−16bn DKK</div>
      <div class="kstat__label">All immigrants &amp; descendants — net annual fiscal balance</div>
      <div class="kstat__source">Finansministeriet 2023</div>
    </div>
    <div class="kstat kstat--cost">
      <div class="kstat__value">−27bn DKK</div>
      <div class="kstat__label">Non-Western immigrants &amp; descendants — net annual cost</div>
      <div class="kstat__source">Finansministeriet 2023</div>
    </div>
    <div class="kstat kstat--contrib">
      <div class="kstat__value">+11bn DKK</div>
      <div class="kstat__label">Western immigrants &amp; descendants — net annual contribution</div>
      <div class="kstat__source">Finansministeriet 2023</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── FAQ ── -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <h2><span class="h2-marker"></span>What does −DKK 16bn mean in practice?</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>The −DKK 16bn aggregate is an average across all immigrants.</strong> It masks a sign reversal between Western and non-Western immigrants. Western immigrants (EU, North America, Australia) contribute +DKK 11bn; non-Western immigrants cost −DKK 27bn.</li>
      <li><strong>Fiscal outcome depends heavily on immigration motive.</strong> Labour migrants generally produce positive contributions; refugees and family reunification migrants produce net costs — a pattern documented across all Nordic countries.</li>
      <li>Finansministeriet uses a <strong>static model</strong> measuring current-year tax and benefit flows. It does not project lifetime contributions, descendants' economic effects, or long-run GDP impacts.</li>
      <li>Denmark is <strong>one of the most transparent countries in the world</strong> for this type of accounting. Equivalent official estimates are published only by Norway (SSB) and Germany (Ifo/IAB) among Western countries.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- ── What about employment trends? ── -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <h2><span class="h2-marker"></span>Has the figure improved since 2019?</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>The 2019 dataset (revised 2023) is the <strong>most recent official calculation</strong> published by Finansministeriet as of 2025.</li>
      <li>Employment of non-Western immigrants has improved: the number of MENAPT-origin workers rose from 62,800 (Q4 2019) to <strong>80,800 (Q4 2024)</strong> — a +29% increase that suggests the net cost has narrowed, but no new official accounting has been published to confirm this.</li>
      <li>A future update would likely show a lower negative balance, but the sign reversal between Western and non-Western immigrants is structural and unlikely to disappear.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Cross-country ── -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <h2><span class="h2-marker"></span>Cross-country comparison</h2>
    <p class="section-note">Direct comparison requires caution — methodologies, scope, and reference years differ significantly.</p>
    <div class="compare-table-wrap">
      <table class="compare-table">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Country</th><th>Official estimate</th><th>Scope</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="row-highlight"><td><strong>Denmark</strong></td><td><strong>−DKK 16bn/year</strong></td><td>All immigrants &amp; descendants</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Norway</td><td>−NOK 4.1m/person (R3 group)</td><td>Asylum &amp; non-European family migration, NPV</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Germany</td><td>−€2.1bn/year</td><td>2015 refugee cohort</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Sweden</td><td>+SEK 6bn/year</td><td>Labour migrants only; total not published</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Primary source ── -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <h2><span class="h2-marker"></span>Primary source</h2>
    <div class="source-block">
      <div class="source-block__icon">📄</div>
      <div>
        <div class="source-block__title">Finansministeriet (2023). <em>Indvandreres nettobidrag til de offentlige finanser i 2019</em> — revised September 2023</div>
        <div class="source-block__links">
          <a href="https://fm.dk/media/5cnhiydz/indvandreres-nettobidrag-til-de-offentlige-finanser-i-2019_revideret-september-2023-a.pdf" rel="noopener" target="_blank">PDF report →</a>
          <a href="https://fm.dk/udgivelser/2023/september/oekonomisk-analyse-indvandreres-nettobidrag-til-de-offentlige-finanser-i-2019-revideret-version-september-2023/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Publication page →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Related navigation ── -->
  <div class="explore-section">
    <div class="explore-section__header">
      <span class="explore-dot"></span>
      <h2>Explore further</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="explore-grid">
      <a href="/en/countries/denmark/" class="explore-card">
        <span class="explore-icon">🇩🇰</span>
        <div>
          <div class="explore-card__title">Denmark — full data</div>
          <div class="explore-card__desc">Demographics, employment, crime, education, housing</div>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="/en/themes/fiscal-cost/" class="explore-card">
        <span class="explore-icon">💰</span>
        <div>
          <div class="explore-card__title">Fiscal cost — 20 countries</div>
          <div class="explore-card__desc">Cross-country net fiscal impact comparison</div>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="/en/themes/comparison-matrix/" class="explore-card">
        <span class="explore-icon">🗂️</span>
        <div>
          <div class="explore-card__title">20-Country Matrix</div>
          <div class="explore-card__desc">All themes at a glance</div>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="/en/faq/denmark-policy-shift/" class="explore-card">
        <span class="explore-icon">⚖️</span>
        <div>
          <div class="explore-card__title">Denmark's policy shift</div>
          <div class="explore-card__desc">Why did Denmark tighten its immigration policy?</div>
        </div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

</div><!-- /faq-body -->

<script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the fiscal cost of immigration in Denmark?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Denmark's Finance Ministry (Finansministeriet 2023) puts the net fiscal cost of all immigrants and descendants at −DKK 16bn/year (2019 data, revised 2023). Broken down: non-Western immigrants and descendants cost −DKK 27bn/year; Western immigrants and descendants contribute +DKK 11bn/year. Denmark is one of the few countries in the world that publishes this type of annual official accounting."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Why does Denmark's immigration fiscal figure differ so much by origin?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The difference is driven primarily by immigration motive and employment rate. Western immigrants (EU, North America, Oceania) arrive mainly as labour migrants with high employment rates and tax contributions. Non-Western immigrants include a higher share of refugees and family reunification migrants with lower initial employment rates and higher social benefit receipt. Finansministeriet documents this breakdown annually."
      }
    }
  ]
}
</script>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
/* ── Hero ── */
.faq-hero {
  max-width: 860px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 3rem 1.5rem 2rem;
  text-align: center;
}

.faq-hero__badge {
  display: inline-block;
  font-size: 0.68rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.13em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--color-accent);
  background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 10%, transparent);
  border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 30%, transparent);
  border-radius: 999px;
  padding: 0.32em 1em;
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}

.faq-hero h1 {
  font-size: clamp(1.7rem, 4.5vw, 2.8rem);
  font-weight: 900;
  line-height: 1.25;
  margin: 0 0 1rem;
  letter-spacing: -0.02em;
}

.faq-hero h1 em {
  font-style: normal;
  color: var(--color-accent);
}

.faq-hero__sub {
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  color: var(--color-ink-soft);
  line-height: 1.8;
  max-width: 36em;
  margin: 0 auto 1.2rem;
}

.faq-hero__meta {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  gap: 0.6rem;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  font-size: 0.78rem;
  color: var(--color-muted);
}

.lang-pill {
  display: inline-block;
  background: var(--color-surface-raised);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  border-radius: 999px;
  padding: 0.25em 0.85em;
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--color-ink-soft);
  text-decoration: none;
}
.lang-pill:hover { border-color: var(--color-primary); color: var(--color-primary); }

.meta-sep { color: var(--color-border); }

/* ── Body ── */
.faq-body {
  max-width: 860px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 0 1.5rem 2rem;
}

/* ── Key stat cards ── */
.key-stats-row {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
  gap: 1rem;
  margin-bottom: 3rem;
}

.kstat {
  border-radius: 10px;
  padding: 1.25rem 1.4rem;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.4rem;
}

.kstat--cost {
  background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 8%, var(--color-surface-raised));
  border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 25%, transparent);
  border-top: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
}

.kstat--contrib {
  background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-teal) 8%, var(--color-surface-raised));
  border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-teal) 25%, transparent);
  border-top: 3px solid var(--color-teal);
}

.kstat__value {
  font-size: 1.9rem;
  font-weight: 900;
  line-height: 1;
  letter-spacing: -0.02em;
}

.kstat--cost .kstat__value { color: var(--color-accent); }
.kstat--contrib .kstat__value { color: var(--color-teal); }

.kstat__label {
  font-size: 0.82rem;
  color: var(--color-ink-soft);
  line-height: 1.45;
}

.kstat__source {
  font-size: 0.65rem;
  color: var(--color-muted);
  margin-top: auto;
  padding-top: 0.5rem;
  border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
}

/* ── Sections ── */
.faq-section {
  margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
}

.faq-section h2 {
  font-size: 1.15rem;
  font-weight: 800;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0.6rem;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

.h2-marker {
  display: inline-block;
  width: 4px;
  height: 1.1em;
  background: var(--color-accent);
  border-radius: 2px;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

.faq-section ul {
  padding-left: 1.4rem;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.65rem;
}

.faq-section li {
  font-size: 0.93rem;
  line-height: 1.75;
  color: var(--color-ink-soft);
}

.faq-section li strong {
  color: var(--color-ink);
}

.section-note {
  font-size: 0.8rem;
  color: var(--color-muted);
  margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
  font-style: italic;
}

/* ── Table ── */
.compare-table-wrap {
  overflow-x: auto;
  border-radius: 10px;
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
}

.compare-table {
  width: 100%;
  border-collapse: collapse;
  font-size: 0.88rem;
}

.compare-table th {
  background: var(--color-surface-raised);
  padding: 0.65rem 1rem;
  text-align: left;
  font-size: 0.72rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--color-muted);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
}

.compare-table td {
  padding: 0.65rem 1rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  color: var(--color-ink-soft);
}

.compare-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }

.row-highlight td {
  background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-gold) 6%, transparent);
  color: var(--color-ink);
}

/* ── Source block ── */
.source-block {
  display: flex;
  gap: 1rem;
  align-items: flex-start;
  background: var(--color-surface-raised);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  border-radius: 10px;
  padding: 1.1rem 1.4rem;
}

.source-block__icon { font-size: 1.4rem; flex-shrink: 0; }

.source-block__title {
  font-size: 0.88rem;
  color: var(--color-ink-soft);
  line-height: 1.6;
  margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
}

.source-block__links {
  display: flex;
  gap: 0.75rem;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}

.source-block__links a {
  font-size: 0.82rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--color-primary);
  text-decoration: none;
}
.source-block__links a:hover { color: var(--color-accent); }

/* ── Explore section ── */
.explore-section {
  border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  padding-top: 1rem;
  margin-top: 1rem;
  padding-bottom: 3rem;
}

.explore-section__header {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0.7rem;
  margin: 1.5rem 0 1.25rem;
}

.explore-dot {
  display: inline-block;
  width: 10px;
  height: 10px;
  background: var(--color-accent);
  border-radius: 2px;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

.explore-section__header h2 {
  font-size: 1.2rem;
  font-weight: 800;
  margin: 0;
}

.explore-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
  gap: 0.75rem;
}

.explore-card {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0.9rem;
  background: var(--color-surface-raised);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  border-radius: 10px;
  padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
  text-decoration: none;
  color: var(--color-ink);
  transition: transform 0.13s, border-color 0.13s;
}
.explore-card:hover {
  transform: translateY(-2px);
  border-color: var(--color-primary);
  color: var(--color-ink);
}

.explore-icon { font-size: 1.5rem; flex-shrink: 0; line-height: 1; }

.explore-card__title {
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--color-primary);
}

.explore-card__desc {
  font-size: 0.78rem;
  color: var(--color-muted);
  margin-top: 0.15rem;
}
</style>
